01 — NuGet.Packaging | CVE-2024-0057
Automatically downloads patched NuGet.Packaging 6.3.1 from BMW Nexus and replaces the vulnerable DLL in Octopus/Calamari on affected VMs.
02 — Kestrel Core | CVE-2025-55315
Scans all VMs for vulnerable Kestrel Core versions (2.x and 8.x), downloads the patched version from BMW Nexus, and updates automatically.
03 — SemanticKernel | CVE-2026-25592
Downloads patched Microsoft.SemanticKernel.Core from BMW Nexus and updates the SSMA for MySQL installation — pending Nexus admin caching the package.
04 — Edge Chromium | CVE-2026-3916
Uses built-in Windows Update to check and install the latest Edge version — no Nexus required, safe to run on any VM.
05 — Commons Collections | CVE-2015-7501
Downloads patched commons-collections JAR from BMW Nexus maven-central and replaces the vulnerable JAR in SQL Server SSIS extensions.
06 — Apache Avro | CVE-2024-47561
Downloads patched Avro JAR from BMW Nexus maven-central and replaces the vulnerable JAR in SQL Server SSIS extensions.
07 — Libcurl | CVE-2023-38545 + CVE-2019-3822
Replaces vulnerable libcurl.dll in FIS Ambit with a patched version — fixes two critical CVEs in one run once patched DLL is staged.
08 — Hadoop Common | CVE-2022-26612
Downloads patched hadoop-common JAR from BMW Nexus maven-central and replaces the vulnerable JAR in SQL Server SSIS extensions.
09 — Windows Server 2022 | CVE-2026-20822
Uses built-in Windows Update/WSUS to apply the latest cumulative security patch — no Nexus required, requires WSUS configured on the VM.
10 — AspNetCore Runtime | CVE-2025-55315
Detects and patches both x86 and x64 vulnerable ASP.NET Core runtime installations in a single run by downloading from BMW Nexus.
